column2: Moderate breeze and sunny.  North shoreline had blue-green algae bloom in localized areas during week of July 3+10th.  When wind was blowing from south bloom became very dense at times.
Exceptional clarity- calm wind- and the secchi line was too short!
Has minor amounts of big algae colonies in water.  They were concentrated down the shoreline.
The water is very cold.  Overcast with at southeast wind at 8-10 mph.
Partly sunny with wind at 8-12 mph.
Light green/cloudy algae (surface) extending 1-2' from shore at various areas.
Sunny with slight haze and calm.
Sunny day- only one other boa (fishing) visible.
Again- beautiful- sunny- warm day- the lake is clear and calm.
Mostly cloudy.  This date sent to national secchi disc depth on 7/8/95.
Mostly sunny day.  Vegetation level in shallow water levels higher this year than in past three years.
Warm- mostly cloudy day.  The water is calm.
Partly sunny and the water is calm.  Very little traffic on this lake over labor day weekend.

Very cool- the temperature is 42 degrees- slight northwest wind with snow showers.  Could not hold the boat with anchor in deep spot.  Used trolling motor- bottom sampler rope verticle- messenger did not always work.
Slight SW wind.  Beautiful clear day- above normal rainy-cloudy days- rainfall is about normal.
August was quite warm and dry.  Lake was clear today- but most of the past 2 weeks has been cloudy.
West wind 10-15 mph.  Partly cloudy.  1.1 inches of rain in the past 24 hours.  28 feet for secchi is the least in 2 years.
Light west wind.  Partly cloudy.  No rain in the past four days.
Partly cloudy- becoming mostly fair.  Light southeast wind at 5 mph- the temperature is 63 degrees.  July to early August was very dry- 20 days with less than one inch of rain.  Summer is over.
Beautiful day- clear sky- mildly warm.  Swimming weather.  Light WNW wind at 5-10 mph.

Cold day- the temperature is 38 degrees.  WSW wind at 8-10 mph.  Mostly cloudy- water was dark.  Lowest Secchi reading of the year.  Lake has just completed turnover.  Assisted by Jim Kliefgen of Bayview Lodge.  The last 30 days have been rainy.
Sunny- calm.  Water clear but small balls of algae present
Sunny- calm- Gleotrichia colony balls in water
NW wind 5-7 mph- Gleotrichia present in water
sunny with slight haze- light winds from SW
Sunnym SW winds 3-5 mph- Gleotrichia "balls" present
Sunny- calm winds.  Some Gleotrichia "balls" present
Partly sunny- hazy overcast.  Winds 10-12 SW
Sunny- wind 3-5 mph from SW Sunny- wind 3-5 mph from SW- a few Gleotrichia colonies observed
Sunny- wind 8-10 from NW- few Gleotrichia colonies present
Partly sunny with thin clouds.  Wind SW 5-7 mph
calm- hazy sunshine calm- hazy sunshine
Overcast- south wind 7-9 mph. Water greenish color with spring phytoplankton
Brownish yellow algae in water. Wind west 8-10 mph
Sunny- wind south southwest 3-5 mph.  Gleotrichia colony balls in water
